org.modelio.metamodel.bpmn.activities

Interface BpmnActivity

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BpmnBaseElement, BpmnFlowElement, BpmnFlowNode, java.lang.Comparable<MObject>, Element, MObject, ModelElement
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    BpmnAdHocSubProcess, BpmnBusinessRuleTask, BpmnCallActivity, BpmnManualTask, BpmnReceiveTask, BpmnScriptTask, BpmnSendTask, BpmnServiceTask, BpmnSubProcess, BpmnTask, BpmnTransaction, BpmnUserTask

    public interface BpmnActivity
extends BpmnFlowNode
    BpmnActivity v0.0.9054 An Activity is work that is performed within a Business Process. An Activity can be atomic or non-atomic (compound). The types of Activities that are a part of a Process are: Task, Sub-Process, and Call Activity, which allows the inclusion of re-usable Tasks and Processes in the diagram. Ownership An activity belongs to a GlowElementContainer or to a sub process.

        boolean isIsForCompensation()
        Getter for attribute 'BpmnActivity.IsForCompensation' Metamodel description: A flag that identifies whether this Activity is intended for the purposes of compensation. If false, then this Activity executes as a result of normal execution flow. If true, this Activity is only activated when a Compensation Event is detected and initiated under Compensation Event visibility scope
